“If they can’t see themselves inside the outcome, they’ll never step into it.”

🧠 DEEPER PSYCHOLOGY BEHIND STATUS BUYING
We pulls from behavioral psychology here:
* Most high-performing people act based on status preservation
* They want to avoid looking stupid, behind, or like they’re guessing
* They fear being seen as struggling more than they fear the cost of solving it
That’s why even smart people will:
* Ghost you when they feel exposed
* Say “I’ll think about it” to avoid the status hit of admitting confusion
* Or only buy when the new identity is more compelling than the safety of the old one

🛠 HOW TO LEVERAGE STATUS IN YOUR SALES CONVERSATION
1. Make the Before Status Explicit
